title: 'PITFALL: Each mapping in a CondElts can be represented many ways, depending on whether they key is included.'
pid: ccbac86a-3e00-49f0-9c1e-db2a33a1845d
body: |2-
  The current idiom is to leave the key out. But -- you could describe a CondElts this way:
   x=1 if (a=1    ) or (b=1    )
  or equivalently, this way:
   x=1 if (a=1,x=1) or (b=1,x=1)
  or this way:
   x=1 if (a=1    ) or (b=1,x=1)
  etc.
